RoutingInfo.AdditionalInformation: For inbound LTE agreement, we expect to receive QCI = 7 from your HSS, if not, the traffic will have a lower priority than standard subscribers. SFR and Bouygues operate on a 4G common Radio Access network. In shared areas, the 20808 is broadcasted but can't be selected by any mobile, so this PLMN shouldn't be used for steering nor for preferred PLMN list in SIM cards. In non shared areas, only the PLMN 20820 is broadcasted. All TAP records generated by Bouygues core network will be produced with FRAF3.
